    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-12T21:18:53+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-12T21:18:53+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-12T11:48:53Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-12T11:48:53Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system in the Tasman Sea maintains a ridge over SA. A cold front near the western border will move across South Australia overnight and into the far northeast on Saturday. A weak high pressure system will immediately follow the cold front and drift eastwards to be over Victoria on Sunday. The high will move over the Tasman Sea on Monday with a northerly flow increasing over SA ahead of a low pressure system that is expected south of the SA coast next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-12T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-13T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-12T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-12T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-13T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-14T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-12T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-13T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers south of Leigh Creek, slight chance elsewhere. Winds northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending northwest to northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h in the morning then tending southeast to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 11 and 14 with daytime temperatures reaching 19 to 30.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:10am to 1:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-14T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-15T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-13T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-14T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers about the Gammon Ranges, slight chance elsewhere. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h turning easterly 15 to 25 km/h during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 27.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-15T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-16T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-14T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-15T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Yunta, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds easterly 15 to 20 km/h turning northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching 21 to 28.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-06-16T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-17T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-15T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-16T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Yunta, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 12 and 17 with daytime temperatures reaching 22 to 29.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
